const summary = [];
summary.push('Dataset ds001_crc contained 50000 patients and outcome pfs_months. The outcome mean was ' + fnum(yMean, 4) + ' months, with range ' + fnum(yRange[0], 4) + ' to ' + fnum(yRange[1], 4) + ' months. I decoded the local Parquet file and used large-sample linear models: binary features were tested as mean differences, continuous or ordinal features as OLS slopes, multivariable models as adjusted OLS, and interactions as centered product terms. Significance was assessed at p<0.05.');
summary.push('The strongest marginal pattern was "'`feature_041`: each one-unit increase was associated with +'"' + fnum(uni.feature_041.effect, 4) + ' months of PFS (' + fp(uni.feature_041.p) + '). Other strong main effects were adverse: "'`feature_025` was '"' + fnum(uni.feature_025.effect, 4) + ' months per level, "'`feature_036=1` was '"' + fnum(uni.feature_036.effect, 4) + ' months versus 0, "'`feature_056` was '"' + fnum(uni.feature_056.effect, 4) + ' months per unit, and "'`feature_029` was '"' + fnum(uni.feature_029.effect, 5) + ' months per unit. Favorable main effects included "'`feature_043=1` (+'"' + fnum(uni.feature_043.effect, 4) + ' months) and "'`feature_050` (+'"' + fnum(uni.feature_050.effect, 4) + ' months per unit).');
summary.push('In the multivariable model adjusting for the ten leading features, the directions were stable: "'`feature_041` +'"' + fnum(adj.feature_041.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_025` '"' + fnum(adj.feature_025.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_036` '"' + fnum(adj.feature_036.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_043` +'"' + fnum(adj.feature_043.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_056` '"' + fnum(adj.feature_056.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_050` +'"' + fnum(adj.feature_050.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_001` '"' + fnum(adj.feature_001.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_015` '"' + fnum(adj.feature_015.coef, 4) + ', "'`feature_029` '"' + fnum(adj.feature_029.coef, 5) + ', and "'`feature_066` '"' + fnum(adj.feature_066.coef, 4) + ' months. All adjusted coefficients had ' + fp(1e-300) + ', indicating that the leading main effects were not explained by one another.');
summary.push('Interaction testing showed clinically meaningful heterogeneity around "'`feature_043`. The `feature_043` advantage was strongly attenuated by `feature_001=1` (interaction '"' + fnum(ints['feature_043:feature_001'].coef, 4) + '), "'`feature_015=1` ('"' + fnum(ints['feature_043:feature_015'].coef, 4) + '), higher "'`feature_029` ('"' + fnum(ints['feature_043:feature_029'].coef, 5) + ' per unit), and "'`feature_066=1` ('"' + fnum(ints['feature_043:feature_066'].coef, 4) + '), all with ' + fp(1e-300) + ' after adjustment. In contrast, "'`feature_043` and `feature_042` had a positive interaction (+'"' + fnum(ints['feature_043:feature_042'].coef, 4) + ' months, ' + fp(ints['feature_043:feature_042'].p) + ').');
summary.push('Additional interactions refined the main effects: the positive "'`feature_041` slope was weaker at higher `feature_025` (interaction '"' + fnum(ints['feature_041:feature_025'].coef, 5) + ') and with "'`feature_036=1` ('"' + fnum(ints['feature_041:feature_036'].coef, 5) + '), while "'`feature_001` and `feature_015` had a positive interaction (+'"' + fnum(ints['feature_001:feature_015'].coef, 4) + '), meaning their combined adverse association was less than additive. "'`feature_001` and `feature_015` penalties also weakened as `feature_029` increased. The `feature_041` by `feature_056` interaction was statistically significant but small ('"' + fnum(ints['feature_041:feature_056'].coef, 6) + ').');
summary.push('Subgroup analyses supported the main conclusions. "'`feature_043=1` was beneficial both when `feature_036=0` (+'"' + fnum(strata.f043_by_f036_0.effect, 4) + ' months) and when "'`feature_036=1` (+'"' + fnum(strata.f043_by_f036_1.effect, 4) + ' months). "'`feature_036=1` was adverse both when `feature_043=0` ('"' + fnum(strata.f036_by_f043_0.effect, 4) + ' months) and when "'`feature_043=1` ('"' + fnum(strata.f036_by_f043_1.effect, 4) + ' months). "'`feature_001=1` was adverse within every `feature_025` level: '"' + fnum(strata.f001_by_f025_0.effect, 4) + ', ' + fnum(strata.f001_by_f025_1.effect, 4) + ', and ' + fnum(strata.f001_by_f025_2.effect, 4) + ' months for "'`feature_025=0`, 1, and 2.'"');
summary.push('Several exploratory hypotheses were not supported. "'`feature_031`, `feature_062`, `feature_051`, `feature_030`, `feature_063`, and `feature_022` showed only weak marginal evidence with p-values from about 0.053 to 0.116. Proposed interactions `feature_036` by `feature_043`, `feature_041` by `feature_042`, and `feature_043` by `feature_050` were also not significant in unadjusted centered interaction tests. Overall, the cohort appears dominated by a strong favorable `feature_041` gradient, adverse `feature_025` and `feature_036` effects, a favorable but highly context-dependent `feature_043` subgroup, and smaller modifiers involving `feature_001`, `feature_015`, `feature_029`, `feature_042`, and `feature_066`.'"');
